Round 1 Q&A

1. Docker and Containerization (In detail)
Q: Explain Docker and containerization.
A:

Docker is a platform to create, deploy, and run applications in containers.

Containers are lightweight, isolated environments sharing the host OS kernel, unlike VMs which have full OS.

Advantages: portability, faster boot time, easy scaling, and dependency isolation.

Core components: Docker Engine, Dockerfile, Images, Containers, Docker Hub, Volumes, Networks.

Commands: docker build, docker run, docker ps, docker stop, docker exec, docker-compose up.



