3. Remove duplicates from an array
Q: Write a Python program to remove duplicates from an array.
A:

list1 = [1,1,1,2,2,2,3,4,4,5]
# Method 1: Using set
unique_list = list(set(list1))
print(unique_list)

# Method 2: Preserving order
unique_list_ordered = []
for i in list1:
    if i not in unique_list_ordered:
        unique_list_ordered.append(i)
print(unique_list_ordered)


