5. AWS S3 & RDS Questions
Q: Explain S3 and RDS.
A:

S3: Object storage, highly durable, scalable, used for files, backups, logs. Supports versioning, bucket policies.

RDS: Managed relational DB (MySQL/Postgres/Oracle), handles backups, patching, scaling, high availability.



