Docker Commands

docker ps – Lists running containers. Add -a to see all containers.

docker images – Shows all local images.

docker build – Builds an image from a Dockerfile. Example: docker build -t myimage .

docker run – Starts a container from an image. Example: docker run -it myimage /bin/bash

docker exec – Runs a command inside a running container. Example: docker exec -it container_id bash

docker logs – Shows logs from a container. Example: docker logs container_id

docker-compose up – Starts all services defined in a docker-compose.yml file.



---

Linux OS Patching

Patching is updating your system to fix security vulnerabilities, bugs, or improve performance.

Ubuntu/Debian:


sudo apt update          # Refresh package lists
sudo apt upgrade         # Apply available updates
sudo reboot              # Reboot if kernel or critical update applied

RHEL/CentOS:


sudo yum update          # Updates all packages
sudo reboot              # If required

Tips:

Always check patch logs: /var/log/yum.log or /var/log/apt/history.log.

Schedule patches during maintenance windows to avoid downtime.

For critical security updates only: apt-get upgrade --only-upgrade package_name or yum update package_name.



